org.pepppt.core

Class Metrics

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.pepppt.core.Metrics

  • public class Metrics
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is a container for the measurements taken in the core.

    • Field Detail

      • NumberOfScans

        public int NumberOfScans
        The number of scans done by the ble scanner. The corresponding KPI is "scancnt"

      • NumberOfAdvertisementsReceived

        public int NumberOfAdvertisementsReceived
        The number of advertisement received from nearby devices. This includes all advertisements with the correct AdvertisementProfile.ManufacturerID. Included are also ads with a wrong ServiceUUID. see NumberOfEncounters. The corresponding KPI is "adsrxcnt"

      • LastAdvertisementTime

        public long LastAdvertisementTime
        The time of the last advertisement. No KPI.

      • NumberOfAdvertisementsReceivedInLastScan

        public int NumberOfAdvertisementsReceivedInLastScan
        The number of received advertisements in the last scan. Included are also ads with a wrong ServiceUUID. see NumberOfEncounters. The corresponding KPI is "adsrxcntls"

      • NumberOfAdvertisementsBroadcasted

        public int NumberOfAdvertisementsBroadcasted
        The number of broadcasted ads. The corresponding KPI is "adstxcnt"

      • NumberOfFailedAdvertisements

        public int NumberOfFailedAdvertisements
        The number of failed advertisements. When the advertisement is send to the bluetooth chip there can be numerous errors. This number is overall counted number. The corresponding KPI is "nofa"

      • NumberOfFailedAdvertisementsAlreadyStarted

        public int NumberOfFailedAdvertisementsAlreadyStarted
        The number of failed advertisements with error ADVERTISE_FAILED_ALREADY_STARTED. The corresponding KPI is "nofaas"

      • NumberOfFailedAdvertisementsDataTooLarge

        public int NumberOfFailedAdvertisementsDataTooLarge
        The number of failed advertisements with error ADVERTISE_FAILED_DATA_TOO_LARGE. The corresponding KPI is "nofadtl"

      • NumberOfFailedAdvertisementsTooManyAdvertisers

        public int NumberOfFailedAdvertisementsTooManyAdvertisers
        The number of failed advertisements with error ADVERTISE_FAILED_TOO_MANY_ADVERTISERS. The corresponding KPI is "nofatma"

      • NumberOfFailedAdvertisementsInternalError

        public int NumberOfFailedAdvertisementsInternalError
        The number of failed advertisements with error ADVERTISE_FAILED_INTERNAL_ERROR. The corresponding KPI is "nofaie"

      • NumberOfFailedAdvertisementsFeatureUnsupported

        public int NumberOfFailedAdvertisementsFeatureUnsupported
        The number of failed advertisements with error ADVERTISE_FAILED_FEATURE_UNSUPPORTED. The corresponding KPI is "nofafu"

      • NumberOfFailedAdvertisementsUnknown

        public int NumberOfFailedAdvertisementsUnknown
        The number of failed advertisements with an unknown error. The corresponding KPI is "nofau"

      • NumberOfEncounters

        public int NumberOfEncounters
        Number of advertisements with correct ServiceUUID and the correct length of 16 bytes. The corresponding KPI is "encs"

      • LastEncounterString

        public java.lang.String LastEncounterString
        A string with last encounter. Looks like this: "[ebid-last-encounter] ([rssi-value])" No KPI.

      • LastEncounterTime

        public long LastEncounterTime
        Time of the last encounter. The KPI "lencdt" will hold the time since the last encounter in minutes.

      • FilteringEnabled

        public boolean FilteringEnabled
        True if the scan filtering is enabled. Should alway be true. No KPI.

      • LastBatchRefresh

        public long LastBatchRefresh
        Time of the last refresh of the ebid list. The KPI "lastbatch" will hold the time since the last batch refresh in minutes.

      • AggregationsCount

        public long AggregationsCount
        The number of calls to the aggregator class from the Fraunhofer IIS. The aggregator will be called every 1 minute by default. The corresponding KPI is "aggcnt"

      • AggregatedResultsCount

        public long AggregatedResultsCount
        The number of overall results received by the aggregator.process. The corresponding KPI is "aggrcnt"

      • AggregatedDataCount

        public long AggregatedDataCount
        The number of overall senders aggregated. The corresponding KPI is "aggdtcnt"

      • EbidsLeftInTheBatch

        public int EbidsLeftInTheBatch
        The number of ebids left in the ebid list. If this number reaches 0 the core will stall and wont process nor broadcast any more. The corresponding KPI is "ebidsib"

      • MaxTimeStall

        public long MaxTimeStall
        The max time in seconds of the stalled core since start of the app. The corresponding KPI is "mts"
